# Hybrid Deployment Walkthrough: SnipLink (Render + Vercel)

I've completed the code updates and pushed them to your repository. The application is now fully prepared for hybrid deployment.

## Deployment Status
- [x] **Backend Logic**: Refactored to support cross-origin navigation.
- [x] **Frontend Logic**: Refactored to target dynamic API URLs.
- [x] **Source Control**: All changes committed and pushed.

## Final Deployment Steps

### 1. Backend (Render)
1. Go to [Render Dashboard](https://dashboard.render.com).
2. Create a **New Web Service** from your GitHub repo.
3. Select the **Docker** runtime (it will use the existing [Dockerfile](file:///c:/Users/Vishnu%20Varthan/Downloads/sniplink/sniplink/Dockerfile)).
4. **Environment Variables**:
   - `SPRING_PROFILES_ACTIVE`: `prod`
   - `JWT_SECRET`: (Any secure random string)
   - `CORS_ORIGINS`: `https://[your-vercel-domain].vercel.app`
   - `APP_BASE_URL`: `https://[your-render-domain].onrender.com`

### 2. Frontend (Vercel)
1. Go to [Vercel Dashboard](https://vercel.com/new).
2. Import your GitHub repo.
3. **Important**: In the [index.html](file:///c:/Users/Vishnu%20Varthan/Downloads/sniplink/sniplink/src/main/resources/static/index.html), [login.html](file:///c:/Users/Vishnu%20Varthan/Downloads/sniplink/sniplink/src/main/resources/static/login.html), [register.html](file:///c:/Users/Vishnu%20Varthan/Downloads/sniplink/sniplink/src/main/resources/static/register.html), and [dashboard.html](file:///c:/Users/Vishnu%20Varthan/Downloads/sniplink/sniplink/src/main/resources/static/dashboard.html) files, you will see a `window.SNIPLINK_API_URL = '';` line.
4. For production, you can set this variable via a Vercel [Environment Variable](https://vercel.com/docs/concepts/projects/environment-variables) or simply update the files to point to your Render URL.

